  â˜ï¸  cloud               Cloud & infrastructure (28 tools) - AWS, K8s, Docker, Terraform
  ğŸ“Š monitoring           System monitoring (18 tools) - htop, ps, btop, osquery
  ğŸ—„ï¸  database            Database tools (8 tools) - usql, mysql, psql, sqlite3
  ğŸ“± mobile               Mobile development (12 tools) - adb, scrcpy, fastboot
  ğŸ” text                 Text processing (35 tools) - ripgrep, jq, awk, sed, grep
  ğŸ§ª testing              Testing & quality (15 tools) - newman, k6, shellcheck

ğŸ” SEARCH EXAMPLES:
  portx search docker           # Find Docker-related tools
  portx search security         # Find security tools
  portx search "json process"   # Multi-word search (use quotes)
  portx search kubernetes       # Find K8s tools

ğŸ› ï¸  TOOL EXAMPLES:
  portx tool aws               # AWS CLI comprehensive guide
  portx tool ripgrep           # Ultra-fast text search
  portx tool kubectl          # Kubernetes management
  portx tool nuclei            # Vulnerability scanner

âŒ¨ï¸  NAVIGATION (in TUI):
  â†‘/â†“ or j/k              Scroll content up/down
  g                       Go to top
  G                       Go to bottom
  /                       Search within current page
  q                       Quit current view
  h                       Show viewer help
  Enter                   Follow links (in directory mode)

ğŸ¯ QUICK START:
  1. portx                     # Start with interactive wiki
  2. portx search <term>       # Find what you need
  3. portx tool <name>         # Get detailed tool docs
  4. portx <category>          # Browse by category

ğŸ“Š STATISTICS:
  â€¢ Total Tools: 493 executables across 8 categories
  â€¢ Success Rate: 99.8% (492/493 tools working)
  â€¢ Directories: 53 organized tool directories
  â€¢ TUI Engine: Glow v2.1.1 with enhanced markdown rendering
  â€¢ Documentation: 500+ pages of comprehensive guides

ğŸ’¡ PRO TIPS:
  â€¢ Start with 'portx' for the full interactive experience
  â€¢ Use search to quickly find tools by keyword
  â€¢ Bookmark useful categories with shell aliases
  â€¢ Combine tools: rg pattern | jq '.field' | bat

EOF
}

# Main command dispatcher
case "${1:-}" in
    ""|"wiki")
        show_tui_manual
        ;;
    "man"|"manual")
        if [[ "$1" == "man" ]]; then
            show_classical_manual
        else
            show_tui_manual
        fi
        ;;
    "search")
        search_manual "$2"
        ;;
    "tool")
        show_tool "$2"
        ;;
    "help"|"--help"|"-h")
        show_help
        ;;
    "filesystem"|"files"|"file"|"core"|"network"|"net"|"security"|"sec"|"development"|"dev"|"cloud"|"infrastructure"|"monitoring"|"system"|"monitor"|"database"|"db"|"mobile"|"android"|"text"|"processing"|"testing"|"test"|"quality")
        show_category "$1"
        ;;
    *)
        echo "Unknown command: $1"
        echo "Use 'portx help' for usage information"
        exit 1
        ;;
esac